article.headline: Arkansas 75, Troy 60
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Senior center Delvon Johnson recorded a double-double with 20 points and 14 rebounds while adding four blocked shots in Arkansas' 75-60 win over Troy Saturday. The Razorbacks (5-1) used a 13-0 run to close the first half. Marvell Waithe's putback at the buzzer gave Arkansas a 48-36 halftime lead. That lead grew to 58-40 early in the second half on a Rotnei Clarke 3-pointer. Troy answered with a 13-2 run of its own midway through the second half to pull within 60-53 with 8:32 remaining, but the Trojans (1-6)could get no closer. Clarke's fourth 3-pointer of the game snapped the scoring burst for the Trojans. Clarke finished with 16 points for Arkansas. Vernon Taylor led Troy with 19 points.
